<p>
    Bedrock comes with a few Handlebars helpers that makes it easier for you to write HTML/CSS.
</p>

<h3 class="content-title" id="localcss"><code>&#123;&#123;addLocalCSS&#125;&#125;</code></h3>
<p>The <code>addLocalCSS</code> helper lets you add local css files on a per-page basis. For example:
</p>
<pre class="code-snippet"><code>&#123;&#123;addLocalCSS "path/to/app.css"&#125;&#125;</code></pre>
<p>The example above will load <code>app.css</code> when the view is rendered.</p>

<h3 class="content-title" id="remotecss"><code>&#123;&#123;addRemoteCSS&#125;&#125;</code></h3>
<p>The <code>addRemoteCSS</code> helper lets you add remote CSS files when the view is rendered.
</p>
<pre class="code-snippet"><code>&#123;&#123;addRemoteCSS "//maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.2.0/css/bootstrap.min.css"&#125;&#125;</code></pre>
<p>The example above will load a new CSS file when the view is rendered.</p>

<h3 class="content-title" id="localjs"><code>&#123;&#123;addLocalJS&#125;&#125;</code></h3>
<p>The <code>addLocalJS</code> helper lets you add local JavaScript files when the view is rendered. For example:
</p>
<pre class="code-snippet"><code>&#123;&#123;addLocalJS "path/to/app.js"}}</code></pre>
<p>The example above will load <code>app.js</code> when the view is rendered.</p>

<h3 class="content-title" id="settitle"><code>&#123;&#123;setTitle&#125;&#125;</code></h3>
<p>The <code>setTitle</code> helper lets you set the HTML <code>&lt;title&gt;</code> attribute for a given view. For example:
</p>
<pre class="code-snippet"><code>&#123;&#123;setTitle "Bedrock - Helpers"}}</code></pre>
